The bus carrying about 54 children veered off the road on Tuesday afternoon. CAPE TOWN Emergency crews have freed a group of pupils who were trapped in a bus on the R304 near Malmesbury.The bus carrying about 54 children veered off the road on Tuesday afternoon.Provincial traffic chief Kenny Africa says they're investigating the cause of the crash. We freed all the children from the bus, and the break down is now busy recovering the bus (sic). The road is still closed and we will take the bus to the weighbridge to do a thorough check. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)